        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>high-strength low-alloy steel [300010923], alloy steel [300010917], steel (alloy) [300133751], iron alloy [300010904], iron and iron alloy [300241605], metal by composition or origin [300010901], metal [300010900], inorganic material [300010360], materials by composition [300212963], materials (substances) [300010358], Materials (hierarchy name) [300010357], Materials Facet [300264091]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A weathering steel that has superior corrosion resistance over regular carbon steel because of a protective oxide film on the metal's surface. Its 50,000 minimum yield strength allows for cost reduction because lighter sections can be designed and built into structures; it is generally meant to be used in unpainted applications where a reduction in maintenance costs, such as painting, are desired. Cor-Ten is a brand name for corrosion resistant products that were developed by United States Steel; Cor-Ten has subsequently been licensed to be produced by other steel manufacturers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Acero para exponer a la intemperie que tiene una resistencia a la corrosión superior a la del acero con carbono habitual, dada la película de óxido protectora que se forma en la superficie del metal. Su resistencia de rendimiento mínima de 50.000 permite reducción de costos, porque se pueden diseñar secciones más livianas para construir estructuras. Se destina en general para aplicaciones sin pintura, donde es importante la reducción de los costos de mantenimiento (como la pintura). Cor-Ten es una marca registrada para productos resistentes a la corrosión desarrollados por la United States Steel; Cor-Ten ha sido licenciada posteriormente para ser producida por otras acerías.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een weerbestendig staal dat beter bestand is corrosie dan normaal koolstofstaal vanwege een beschermende oxidelaag op het staaloppervlak. De vloeigrens van minimaal 50.000 is kostenbesparend omdat lichtere delen kunnen worden ontwikkeld en opgebouwd tot structuren. Het is bedoeld voor gebruik in ongeschilderde toepassingen waar een besparing op onderhoudskosten, zoals schilderen, gewenst is. Cor-Ten is een merknaam voor corrosiebestendige producten die zijn ontwikkeld door United States Steel; Cor-Ten is vervolgens in licentie vrijgegeven voor productie door andere staalfabrikanten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052374/Polytechnisch woordenboek En-Ne (1991)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種可耐天候的鋼，其金屬表面帶有保護性氧化物薄膜，因此抗腐蝕力優於一般碳鋼。其最小降伏強度（minimum yield strength）達每平方英吋五萬磅（即340,000千帕），有助於降低成本，因為可在建築時採用相對較輕的構造設計。通常在建造未上漆結構物時使用戈坦鋼，是希望能降低維護所需成本（如可不用粉刷）。「戈坦」是美國鋼廠（United States Steel）為其發明之抗腐蝕鋼料所取的商標名稱，隨後其他鋼鐵製造廠也獲得許可生產戈坦鋼。   </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Um aço de intemperismo que possui resistência superior à corrosão em relação ao aço carbono comum devido a uma película de óxido de proteção na superfície do metal. Sua resistência mínima de 50.000 permite redução de custos, pois seções mais leves podem ser projetadas e incorporadas em estruturas; geralmente é para ser usado em aplicações não pintadas, onde é desejada uma redução nos custos de manutenção, como pintura. Cor-Ten é um nome de marca para produtos resistentes à corrosão, desenvolvidos pela United States Steel; O Cor-Ten foi posteriormente licenciado para ser produzido por outros fabricantes de aço.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
